Fail.
If $|S|=5$, $|U|=1$.
Adversary picks $E$. $E$ has at most 1 from $U$.
$A$ has 2 questions. $A$ has at most 1 from $U$.
So $A$ has at least 1 from $S$.
$B$ has 2 questions. $B$ has at most 1 from $U$.
So $B$ has at least 1 from $S$.
Student succeeds.

Answer is 5.

